<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="1189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1189">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79641/8–2145: Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 1189<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Chief of the Aviation
                                        Division</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MSW2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1189fn1">Sent to the American Embassy,
                                        London.</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                                </opener>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-21T18:00:00-04:00">August 21, 1945—6 p.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>7101. For <persName corresp="#p_MSW2">Stokeley
                                    Morgan</persName>.</p>
                                <p>Potsdam meeting did not go into aviation questions except for
                                    statement from Secretary to <persName corresp="#p_CHSA1">Cadogan</persName> that discussion of problem was
                                        desired.…<note n="2" xml:id="d1189fn2">No other papers
                                        relating to this <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_CHSA1">Cadogan</persName> conversation have been found.
                                        Concerning a <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> conversation on this subject,
                                        however, see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_80">p. 80</ref>.</note></p>
                                <closer><signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></persName>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_BJO1">J[ohn] B[ell]</persName>
                                    </signed></closer>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>